                    "value": "<p>A creature damaged by the banshee's touch that isn't already @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened] must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:38] save (DC 43 if the attack was a critical hit). If the creature fails its save, it's @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 2}; on a critical failure, the creature also cowers with fear and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stunned]{Stunned 4}. If the creature is protected against fear by a spell or magic item, the banshee's touch first attempts to counteract the protection effect, with the effect of a 9th-level <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Dispel Magic]</em> spell.</p>"
